<div class="rules-container">
    <div class="rules-header">Ongoing Maintenance</div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <p>
            Caring for the resting place of our loved ones is a sacred trust. Paradise Avenue Muslim Cemetery is committed to maintaining a peaceful, clean, and dignified environment, in accordance with Islamic principles of respect for the deceased.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Our Daily Responsibilities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Groundskeeping:</strong> Regular mowing, edging, and landscape care.</li>
            <li><strong>Grave Plot Maintenance:</strong> Keeping all plots level, neat, and undisturbed.</li>
            <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Upkeep of fences, signs, water taps, and walkways.</li>
            <li><strong>Cleanliness:</strong> Continuous removal of leaves, trash, or any unauthorized decorations.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Why It Matters</h3>
        <p>
            A clean and well-maintained cemetery not only honors those who have passed, but provides a serene and reflective environment for their families and visitors. It is part of our duty as Muslims to uphold dignity in all affairs concerning the deceased.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="note-box">
        <strong>Your Support Matters:</strong> As a nonprofit cemetery, we rely on your donations and volunteer support. Any contribution you make—financial or time—is a form of <em>Sadaqah Jaariyah</em> (ongoing charity) that benefits you even after your passing. May Allah (SWT) reward you generously.
    </div>
</div>

